<div class="info">Welcome to the paper submission system for HotCloud 2012!<br />

Some important considerations:
<ul>
<li>You can upload a new version at any time before the deadline, as well as change the title, authors, etc., so we strongly suggest that you upload a version of your paper early on and submit revisions incrementally, rather than leaving it to the last minute.</li>
<li>References do not need to be set in the same-sized font as the body text. (The USENIX LaTeX style uses \footnotesize, so it seemed easiest to change the requirements rather than the style. This means that you may see format violations from the last page in the automated format checker.)</li>
<li>Details of the submission requirements can be found <a href="http://static.usenix.org/events/hotcloud12/cfp/">here</a>. The automated format checker can help you determine if you meet them, but the submission rules are what dominates, not what the checker says.</li>
<li>There will be no extensions for "I'm sorry, I didn't realize this."</li>
</ul></div>
